text: Crab Wood is a biological Site of Special Scientific Interest west of Winchester in Hampshire. An area of is also a Local Nature Reserve. This site has been wooded at least since the sixteenth century. It has a hazel layer which has been coppiced, large oaks and some beech, ash and birch trees. There is a rich butterfly fauna, including purple emperors. ==References== Category:Local Nature Reserves in Hampshire Category:Sites of Special Scientific Interest in Hampshire
title: Crab Wood
